uk.co.strangeskies.reflection

Class AnnotatedTypes

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.co.strangeskies.reflection.AnnotatedTypes

  • public final class AnnotatedTypes
extends java.lang.Object
    A collection of general utility methods relating to annotated types within the Java type system. Utilities related to more specific classes of annotated type may be found in AnnotatedWildcardTypes, AnnotatedParameterizedTypes, and AnnotatedArrayTypes.

      A parser for AnnotatedTypes, and various related types.

      • toString

        public static java.lang.String toString(java.lang.reflect.AnnotatedType annotatedType,
                                        Imports imports)
        Give a canonical String representation of a given annotated type, which is intended to be more easily human-readable than implementations of Object.toString() for certain implementations of Type. Provided class and package imports allow the names of some classes to be output without full package qualification.
        Parameters:
        annotatedType - The type of which we wish to determine a string representation.
        imports - Classes and packages for which full package qualification may be omitted from output.
        Returns:
        A canonical string representation of the given type.
